1
00:00:01,167 --> 00:00:02,567
<i>They said you can apply
for the scholarship again!</i>

2
00:00:02,567 --> 00:00:04,633
<i>You didn't even ask
for my opinion.</i>

3
00:00:04,633 --> 00:00:06,567
<i> I just want to support you.</i>

4
00:00:06,567 --> 00:00:08,333
<i> Even if you kill me...</i>

5
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:10,567
<i> I didn't kill Juan...</i>

6
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:12,367
<i> It's Andy Arellano.</i>

7
00:00:12,367 --> 00:00:13,433
<i> Because of the treasure.</i>

8
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:15,367
This means we have to do better

9
00:00:15,367 --> 00:00:17,033
<i>to keep putting pressure
on Andy.</i>

10
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:18,667
<i>We already told them
we have clues. What else?</i>

11
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:21,533
Isn't it better to pay our debt
<i> to him instead?</i>

12
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:24,000
<i> He needs to think
that</i> we have a lot of money.

13
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,633
<i>And he should feel that we're
hiding something from him.</i>

14
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:29,267
<i>You're paying me?
The hotel is earning money.</i>

15
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:30,700
<i> We got lucky.</i>

16
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:32,633
<i>It doesn't matter
where we got the money.</i>

17
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:34,567
<i>What's important is
we're paying you back.</i>

18
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:41,667
Luna messaged me.

19
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:43,667
She already paid Andy.

20
00:00:44,367 --> 00:00:45,700
He asked
if the hotel is earning money.

21
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,600
- Is that all?
- Yes.

22
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,333
He's still wondering.

23
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:53,467
Especially when he hears
we're having a celebration.

24
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:56,300
For sure,
he's still keeping an eye on us.

25
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,033
[MONETTE]
Guys, have some coffee.

27
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:01,367
- Come on.
- Sure.

28
00:01:01,367 --> 00:01:02,467
Perfect timing.

29
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,233
Thank you, Monette

30
00:01:04,233 --> 00:01:05,333
Anything for you guys.

31
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:06,533
[CUPS CLINK]

32
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,300
<i>That family has been
arrogant ever since.</i>

33
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:11,300
<i> It might not be true.</i>

34
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:12,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:15,567
<i>But where did they get
the money to pay me?</i>

36
00:01:15,567 --> 00:01:18,067
[WAVES CRASHING]

37
00:01:18,067 --> 00:01:18,800
[GLASS THUDS]

38
00:01:20,067 --> 00:01:22,333
[PHONE RINGING]

39
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:26,233
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

40
00:01:26,233 --> 00:01:27,167
What?

41
00:01:27,167 --> 00:01:28,600
[ANDY]
<i> Look, I know you're still mad</i>

42
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,467
<i>because of how
our last conversation ended.</i>

43
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:32,600
Just say it, Dad.

44
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:34,700
What do you want?

45
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:40,233
[EXHALES]

46
00:01:40,233 --> 00:01:42,233
Where did they
find the treasure?

47
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,733
I don't know.

48
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:46,100
I don't know anything.

49
00:01:46,567 --> 00:01:49,400
[SIGHS] Edward, please.
This is important.

50
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,167
You need to tell me
so I'll know my next move.

51
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:53,800
What do you mean?

52
00:01:54,833 --> 00:01:56,067
Who?

53
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:59,200
Who will you kill next
after Juan?

54
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:01,167
I didn't kill Juan.

55
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:04,100
I may be a lot of things,
but I'm not a murderer.

56
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:05,400
Sure.

57
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:07,367
Keep telling yourself that

58
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:10,267
until you're convinced
of your own lies.

59
00:02:10,267 --> 00:02:12,500
Edward, please listen to me.

60
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,133
Enough!

61
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:17,267
I've already left your home,
and you still keep bothering me!

62
00:02:17,767 --> 00:02:20,600
<i>Why don't you just
answer my question?</i>

63
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,267
Where did they find
the treasure?

64
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:24,400
I don't know!

65
00:02:25,267 --> 00:02:27,333
Jade and I
haven't spoken for days.

66
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,200
Why?

67
00:02:30,133 --> 00:02:31,233
Did they forbid you?

68
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:32,833
Because I decided

69
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:36,400
to stop talking to her
because of your lies.

70
00:02:40,867 --> 00:02:47,800
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WAVES CRASHING]

71
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:53,167
[GRUNTING IMPATIENTLY]

72
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,467
<i> This can't happen.</i>

73
00:02:58,867 --> 00:03:01,633
<i> I need to get the treasure.</i>

74
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:06,400
But first...

75
00:03:07,567 --> 00:03:09,267
I have one last thing to finish.

76
00:03:09,267 --> 00:03:11,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

77
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:18,833
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

78
00:04:11,767 --> 00:04:14,867
[CUTLERY CLINKING]

79
00:04:14,867 --> 00:04:16,367
You still hungry? Here.

80
00:04:16,367 --> 00:04:17,533
Eat mine.

81
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:18,467
Why?

82
00:04:18,467 --> 00:04:20,467
- You look hungry.
- [MARTIN CHUCKLES]

83
00:04:20,467 --> 00:04:23,800
I've no idea where you put
all that food, Kiko.

84
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:26,267
Are you going
to eat that, Martin?

85
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,533
[MARTIN] Oh god. Here.

86
00:04:28,567 --> 00:04:30,033
- There.
- Thank you.

87
00:04:30,033 --> 00:04:32,267
[CUTLERY CLINKS]

88
00:04:33,567 --> 00:04:34,933
Time really flew by fast.

89
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:38,967
I remember bringing Sir Mike
his coffee.

90
00:04:38,967 --> 00:04:40,333
Now it's you guys.

91
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:42,767
- [GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [KIKO CHUCKLES]

92
00:04:42,767 --> 00:04:44,367
Nostalgia's hitting you, huh?

93
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,333
[MARTIN CHUCKLES]

94
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:46,667
No, it's just that

95
00:04:46,667 --> 00:04:49,833
I thought I'd stop
bringing coffee here.

96
00:04:50,633 --> 00:04:52,267
Ever since...

97
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:54,233
he died.

98
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:57,400
I thought...

99
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:01,433
I thought we'd lose Hotel 88.

100
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:05,933
Luckily, you guys are here.

101
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,700
You managed to keep the hotel.

102
00:05:09,567 --> 00:05:11,467
Honestly, I didn't expect

103
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:12,900
I'd fight for it till the end.

104
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:15,700
If not for these two,

105
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,333
I would've given up
a long time ago.

106
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:20,267
[TONGUE CLICKS, EXHALES]
Sorry.

107
00:05:20,867 --> 00:05:22,433
I just remembered Raphie.

108
00:05:23,967 --> 00:05:26,500
I just think he's stuck here
on the island.

109
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:30,933
I wish I had supported
him earlier...

110
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:35,267
so he could see
a different world.

111
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,633
Oh, Monette.

112
00:05:37,633 --> 00:05:39,467
Raphie can still do all that.

113
00:05:39,467 --> 00:05:42,100
If you want to, just tell me.
I can take him there.

114
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:44,033
Mm-hmm.
If Raphie wants to go to Manila,

115
00:05:44,033 --> 00:05:45,267
I'll help him.

116
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:47,600
And for sure,
Trixie will look after him, too.

117
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,400
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

118
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:50,733
If he thinks staying
at Martin's is too fancy,

119
00:05:50,733 --> 00:05:52,533
he can stay
with Mommy La and me.

120
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:54,100
I'm sure they'll get along well.

121
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:55,433
Sounds good too.

122
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:56,700
[MONETTE EXHALES]

123
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:58,467
Thank you, guys.

124
00:05:58,467 --> 00:06:00,833
[SNIFFLES, BREATHES SHARPLY]

125
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:02,333
At least...

126
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:05,833
I'd be relieved that
even though I'm not by his side,

127
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:09,300
he'll have a family
he can lean on.

128
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,100
- Oh, Monette.
- Aw, Monette.

129
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:15,667
Raphie is just going to Manila.

130
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:17,500
You'll not be apart
for too long.

131
00:06:18,667 --> 00:06:20,367
Hey, but promise me...

132
00:06:21,567 --> 00:06:23,967
while I'm away, you'll always
look after Raphie.

133
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:26,400
[KIKO] I promise.

134
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:28,867
[MONETTE BREATHES DEEPLY]

135
00:06:28,867 --> 00:06:31,367
Hey, stop it, Kiko.
You're making Monette cry.

136
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:32,800
Seriously, Kiko?
Why are you like this?

137
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,100
- Look at her. She's crying.
- W-Why is it my fault?

138
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:39,067
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

139
00:06:39,067 --> 00:06:40,100
[KIKO] l'll take care of it.

140
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,733
[SARI] Ooh.

141
00:06:41,767 --> 00:06:43,500
We're florists.

142
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:45,967
[TRIXIE]
I love it. I love flowers.

143
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:47,433
[JADE CHUCKLES]

144
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:49,400
I hope our efforts
don't go in vain.

145
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:53,000
Don't worry, for sure,
Andy Arellano is baffled.

146
00:06:54,867 --> 00:06:56,167
- That's cuter.
- There's contrast.

147
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,400
Can we talk?

148
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,467
I think the big one
would look better, too.

149
00:06:59,467 --> 00:07:00,800
- This.
- Yes.

150
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,033
- Jade.
- I don't think so...

151
00:07:02,033 --> 00:07:03,800
- Three of these?
- Oh, three?

152
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,033
Yes, these ones...

153
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:09,033
[GIO GRUNTS] Argh! Excuse me.

154
00:07:09,567 --> 00:07:10,700
[MARTIN] Sari.

155
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:13,667
Jade, we haven't had
the chance to talk.

156
00:07:13,667 --> 00:07:14,767
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

157
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,733
You expect me to talk to you
after telling on me?

158
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:19,867
Jade, I'm sorry.

159
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:23,500
I did that because
I was worried about you

160
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:24,733
and our families.

161
00:07:25,733 --> 00:07:27,400
Don't you trust me?

162
00:07:28,167 --> 00:07:30,033
I thought we were best friends.

163
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,567
Jade, I trust you,

164
00:07:31,567 --> 00:07:32,867
but I don't trust Edward.

165
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,067
You're my best friend,
and Edward isn't.

166
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:37,100
It's different with you, Jade.
And same goes with Edward.

167
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:40,067
Kiko, his father's sins
aren't his.

168
00:07:40,067 --> 00:07:41,833
Then you shouldn't have been
mad at me

169
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:44,100
when you thought
Papa killed Uncle Fred.

170
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,867
Because it's not my fault,
am I right?

171
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:51,500
You're saying I'm complicit
in my father's doing,

172
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,533
- but with Edward, he isn't?
- It's completely different.

173
00:07:56,633 --> 00:07:57,667
Okay, Jade.

174
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:00,500
How is it different?

175
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,767
I don't know, Kiko.

176
00:08:06,033 --> 00:08:07,167
For me...

177
00:08:08,033 --> 00:08:09,100
it's different.

178
00:08:15,067 --> 00:08:16,067
Let's get back.

179
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:21,900
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

180
00:08:21,933 --> 00:08:28,233
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

181
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:29,233
[MUSIC FADES]

182
00:08:29,233 --> 00:08:30,767
Sir! Sir!

183
00:08:30,767 --> 00:08:31,800
You need to see this.

184
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:38,000
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,267
[JUAN] Let me go!

186
00:08:39,267 --> 00:08:43,767
[JUAN GRUNTING]
<i> Argh! Argh! Argh!</i>

187
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:45,100
[COP 1]
That's Juan Soliman, right?

188
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:49,533
[GRUNTING CONTINUES]

189
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,233
[WOMAN] That's what you get
from trying to escape.

190
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:57,100
Marina?

191
00:08:58,533 --> 00:08:59,567
[MARINA] Oh.

192
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:01,867
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

193
00:09:01,867 --> 00:09:03,200
Let's have coffee first.

194
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,600
These are for you.

195
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:09,067
Hey! What are you watching?

196
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,500
You guys.

197
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,600
[REATHING HEAVILY]

198
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,567
[CUP THUDS]

199
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,533
You killed Juan?

200
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,767
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

201
00:09:35,267 --> 00:09:36,633
N-No!

202
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:38,133
T-That's not me!

203
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:38,967
That's not true!

204
00:09:38,967 --> 00:09:40,667
It's fake!
Where did you get it?!

205
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:43,000
Delete it! That's not me!

206
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,133
That's not true!

207
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:46,100
T-That's not me!

208
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,067
Syvera...

209
00:09:49,067 --> 00:09:52,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

210
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:54,267
[GUN CLICKS]

211
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:56,200
Don't move.

212
00:09:57,867 --> 00:09:58,933
Calm down.

213
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,600
- Don't move!
- Marina, let's talk.

214
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:03,300
Let's talk about it.

215
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:07,600
- Don't move!
- [HENRI] Marina, let's talk.

216
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:10,100
Let's fix this.
Put the gun down.

217
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,933
[MARINA BREATHING HEAVILY]

218
00:10:11,933 --> 00:10:13,367
Marina!

219
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:14,333
Report her.

220
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,400
Let's go!

221
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:23,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,533
[GATES CREAK, CLANG]

223
00:10:45,433 --> 00:10:52,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:11:07,433 --> 00:11:14,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

225
00:11:14,133 --> 00:11:18,467
- [LINE RINGS]
- [PHONE RINGS]

226
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,167
Hello?

227
00:11:20,167 --> 00:11:22,500
You bastard! You betrayed me!

228
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:27,133
- What are you talking about?
- You sent the video.

229
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:28,600
The one about Juan's murder.

230
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,667
Syvera and the others saw it!

231
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:32,800
Do you think I'm stupid enough
to send that?

232
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,900
I have nothing to do
with what you're saying.

233
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:37,633
No one else could send that,
but you!

234
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:40,033
You know,
instead of talking to me,

235
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:43,400
you should start hiding.
Leave Kaluguran.

236
00:11:43,433 --> 00:11:45,500
[MARINA] For what?
So you can save yourself?

237
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,100
Damn you, Andy.

238
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,567
If I go down,
I'm taking you with me!

239
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:54,867
Mari--

240
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:59,600
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

241
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:04,033
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

242
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:07,800
[DOOR KNOB CLICKS]

243
00:12:09,167 --> 00:12:16,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

244
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:29,467
[CUTLERY CLINKING]

245
00:12:30,867 --> 00:12:33,000
Cheska, we need one more glass.

246
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:37,033
[MONETTE CHUCKLES]

247
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:40,000
Since when have you been Korean?

248
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:43,500
I don't need to be Korean
to complete a heart...

249
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,633
...when you're its other half.

250
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,600
You're my brother!

251
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:51,833
Stop it, Monette. You're unfair.

252
00:12:52,733 --> 00:12:54,200
Don't be angry anymore.

253
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,833
I only did that
because we're siblings.

254
00:12:57,833 --> 00:13:00,267
I want your dreams
to come true.

255
00:13:00,267 --> 00:13:03,167
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

256
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:04,167
[RAPHIE SIGHS]

257
00:13:07,733 --> 00:13:08,967
Fine.

258
00:13:08,967 --> 00:13:11,000
If you really don't want to,
I'm not going to force you.

259
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,467
But don't you really want it?

260
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:16,467
- Because...
- Because?

261
00:13:18,033 --> 00:13:20,133
Because I don't want
to leave you here, Monette.

262
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,200
[MONETTE SIGHS]

263
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,000
But you do want it?

264
00:13:28,167 --> 00:13:29,967
Then go!

265
00:13:29,967 --> 00:13:32,500
Go study fashion design.

266
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,667
But what about you?

267
00:13:36,767 --> 00:13:38,267
What about me?

268
00:13:38,267 --> 00:13:40,133
I'll be here at Hotel 88!

269
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:42,600
You know I have nowhere else
to go.

270
00:13:43,267 --> 00:13:44,833
And wouldn't that be better?

271
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:47,067
You won't have any trouble
coming to me.

272
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:51,033
But what if you come with me?

273
00:13:52,167 --> 00:13:53,167
Raphie...

274
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,933
My heart is here
on this island.

275
00:13:58,067 --> 00:14:00,667
Your heart is in your talents.

276
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:04,300
I don't want to stop
your heart's desires

277
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:05,933
just to follow mine.

278
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:07,967
Hm?

279
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:13,033
We'll still be siblings
even when we're far apart.

280
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:16,700
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:18,067
I love you, Monette.

282
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:20,200
[RAPHIE SNIFFLES]

283
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:22,100
You're so annoying!

284
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:24,733
You've done nothing
but love me.

285
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:26,300
What do you mean
I've done nothing?

286
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:29,900
- I cook, I manage the hotel--
- Monette.

287
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:32,733
But, of course, my top priority
is to love you.

288
00:14:32,733 --> 00:14:34,967
[MONETTE CHUCKLES]

289
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:37,733
Just remember
to be careful out there, okay?

290
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:40,033
Be careful.

291
00:14:42,233 --> 00:14:43,800
There are a lot
of bad people.

292
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:48,033
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

293
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:49,667
- Thank you, Monette.
- Hmm...

294
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:50,867
- Thank you.
- Come here.

295
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:54,100
I love you so, so, so much!

296
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:56,900
- I love you!
- I love you!

297
00:14:58,267 --> 00:14:59,667
Damn you, Andy.

298
00:14:59,667 --> 00:15:04,200
[BREATHING RAPIDLY]

299
00:15:06,633 --> 00:15:07,667
[GUN COCKS]

300
00:15:10,167 --> 00:15:15,167
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

301
00:15:15,167 --> 00:15:16,133
[GUN COCKS]

302
00:15:24,033 --> 00:15:25,800
Do you think Andy's coming?

303
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,067
[JADE] You think
Uncle Andy did do it?

304
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:29,300
We purposefully made him hear
that there's a celebration.

305
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:31,900
It'll make him think.

306
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,033
If he comes, then he comes.

307
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:38,133
If he doesn't, that's fine too.

308
00:15:39,267 --> 00:15:40,400
For now,
we should take advantage

309
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:41,933
of all of us being here.

310
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:46,100
So that if Andy hears we're okay
despite his threats...

311
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,300
He'll get more frustrated.

312
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,733
Sir Martin! Sir Martin!

313
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:55,067
- It's Henri.
- Sir Henri.

314
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:57,700
Is there a problem, sir?

315
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:00,200
[HENRI] I'm sorry
for disrupting.

316
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,267
Do you have any news for us?

317
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:07,133
I just want to report that we
discovered Juan's real killer.

318
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,133
Who?

319
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:12,800
Marina De La Paz.

320
00:16:13,733 --> 00:16:15,867
The cop? Your partner?

321
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,200
Then we're right!

322
00:16:19,033 --> 00:16:21,233
There's a video
of her shooting Juan...

323
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:22,800
...that led to his death.

324
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:26,800
This is strong evidence,
so Leon's now exonerated.

325
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:31,233
Sir, she's working with Andy.

326
00:16:31,233 --> 00:16:32,800
[HENRI] We can't be sure
about that,

327
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,033
but we'll investigate on it.

328
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,933
[JADE] Sir!

329
00:16:36,933 --> 00:16:40,933
Does this mean
we can finally be with Leon?

330
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,500
[HENRI] Once the judge sees
the evidence

331
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:46,833
that he's not the killer,
his case will be dismissed.

332
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:49,167
I'll call Mom!
This is good news!

333
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:52,133
[HENRI] If you know
where Leon is,

334
00:16:52,133 --> 00:16:54,233
please tell him to show himself.

335
00:16:54,233 --> 00:16:57,767
[LUNA] Sir, this is great news.
Thank you very much.

336
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:01,267
[HENRI] I also came here
to tell you to be careful.

337
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,833
We still haven't
found De La Paz.

338
00:17:04,833 --> 00:17:07,300
She might come here,
and cause trouble.

339
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:09,400
Sir, we'll report it
to you immediately.

340
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:12,100
We won't let De La Paz
set foot on this island.

341
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:15,167
Alright. I'll get going.

342
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,400
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

343
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,767
- Thank you.
- Thank you, sir.

344
00:17:22,633 --> 00:17:24,033
[FRIDA EXHALES DEEPLY]
<i> Thanks be to God.</i>

345
00:17:24,233 --> 00:17:25,400
Okay then.

346
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:27,000
Go call your brother!

347
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,167
[JUSTIN]<i> Yes. Luna said
</i> she'd call him.

348
00:17:29,167 --> 00:17:31,167
<i> Mom, this is great news!</i>

349
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:32,767
I know. I know.

350
00:17:32,767 --> 00:17:35,133
We'll finally be together
with Leon.

351
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:37,467
Okay then, I still have
to call the lawyer.

352
00:17:37,467 --> 00:17:40,133
Celebrate your brother's life.

353
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:41,467
[JUSTIN] Okay, Mom.

354
00:17:41,467 --> 00:17:44,467
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

355
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:45,667
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

356
00:17:45,667 --> 00:17:48,067
You know, as soon as
De La Paz gets caught,

357
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,067
Andrew Arellano's involvement
will also be found.

358
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:53,967
He will pay for all the crimes
he committed against our family.

359
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:57,300
The most important thing now
is that Leon is finally free.

360
00:17:58,100 --> 00:17:59,467
Luna, has he still not answered?

361
00:17:59,867 --> 00:18:01,833
[LUNA] Not yet. I've been
calling him since earlier.

362
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:04,000
I tried calling him the day
before yesterday.

363
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,233
The line was ringing but
he wasn't answering my calls.

364
00:18:06,233 --> 00:18:08,367
I had just called his condo.

365
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:10,167
[MARTIN] The staff said
Leon hasn't come there yet.

366
00:18:10,167 --> 00:18:12,267
Could something have
happened to him?

367
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:14,067
Well, I hope not.

368
00:18:14,067 --> 00:18:15,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:17,833
I know you want to talk
to Leon right now.

370
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:19,233
But while he still
can't be contacted,

371
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:21,367
may we resume
our thanksgiving first?

372
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:24,300
Let's be grateful for
the good news.

373
00:18:25,267 --> 00:18:26,867
[GIO] Justin, are you good?

374
00:18:26,867 --> 00:18:28,500
[RAPHIE] Sure, Miss Jade.

375
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:30,100
- Dig in.
- Monette!

376
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:30,967
[RAPHIE] That's delicious.

377
00:18:30,967 --> 00:18:33,100
I want that one.
That's my favorite.

378
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:35,500
[GIGGLING]

379
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:39,000
[RAPHIE] Oh! My sister is
having her emotional moment.

380
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,400
- Oh stop.
- Come on, Monette. Sit with us.

381
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:44,233
Don't bother taking care of us.
Let's just eat together.

382
00:18:44,233 --> 00:18:46,767
- I'm just happy to see you.
- I'm just happy to see you.

383
00:18:46,767 --> 00:18:48,933
- [LAUGHING]
- I already knew what she'd say.

384
00:18:48,933 --> 00:18:51,067
That's just how she is.
Oh, sister.

385
00:18:51,067 --> 00:18:53,467
That's just what I really feel.

386
00:18:53,467 --> 00:18:55,300
[RAPHIE] You're always
acting like that.

387
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:57,167
You act like everything's
about happy memories.

388
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,400
Of course.

389
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:02,033
We all have happy memories
here at the hotel, don't we?

390
00:19:02,033 --> 00:19:04,500
- Mm!
- [MONETTE] Okay, wait.

391
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:07,067
Since we're celebrating today...

392
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:10,033
we'll each say
our happy memories here.

393
00:19:10,033 --> 00:19:13,000
- [WHINING]
- Come on, game!

394
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:15,333
I have a lot of happy memories,
so I'm going to go first.

395
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:16,900
Mm...

396
00:19:17,567 --> 00:19:21,167
I grew up in this hotel
so I think, for me,

397
00:19:21,167 --> 00:19:24,000
it's the time I spent
being with my sister.

398
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:30,967
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

399
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:34,100
What about you, Cheska?

400
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:36,100
I think it might be...

401
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:38,233
seeing my brother...

402
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,933
who always act like big brother
to us in our home,

403
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:42,333
be the youngest one
here at the hotel.

404
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:43,933
- Yes!
- Wow!

405
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:45,933
- [GIO] Baby bro!
- [MARTIN] Baby bro!

406
00:19:45,933 --> 00:19:47,867
- Baby bro!
- [LAUGHING]

407
00:19:47,867 --> 00:19:51,867
[CHESKA] Of course, at home,
he would look after us.

408
00:19:51,867 --> 00:19:56,167
<i>But here at the hotel, he's
the one being looked after.</i>

409
00:19:56,167 --> 00:19:59,133
- [LAUGHING]
- That's our baby.

410
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,000
How about you, girl?

411
00:20:02,033 --> 00:20:03,967
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

412
00:20:03,967 --> 00:20:05,567
I'd say...

413
00:20:05,967 --> 00:20:07,533
it would be having
a friend here.

414
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:10,067
- [CHESKA] Really? Who is it?
- [TRIXIE] Mm-hmm.

415
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:11,500
It's Kiko.

416
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:12,533
Oh! You guys are close, Kiko?

417
00:20:12,533 --> 00:20:15,500
- She's kidding.
- Of course, it's you! Who else?

418
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:18,333
[LAUGHING]

419
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:21,500
[TRIXIE] Well, to be honest,
back in Manila,

420
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:23,467
I didn't have a lot of friends.

421
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:27,267
<i>I only got to experience here
what it means to have someone...</i>

422
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:28,500
I can call my constant.

423
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:29,867
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

424
00:20:29,867 --> 00:20:31,267
- Thank you.
- [CHESKA CLICKS TONGUE]

425
00:20:31,267 --> 00:20:33,267
[CHUCKLING]

426
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:34,400
[KIKO] Constant?

427
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,567
- You, really?
- [GIGGLING]

428
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:38,167
- Ouch.
- What about you, Justin?

429
00:20:39,967 --> 00:20:42,100
My happiest memory here?

430
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:45,333
[JUSTIN] It's that I made
two new friends.

431
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:48,033
[TRIXIE] I enjoyed the adventure
we three had.

432
00:20:48,033 --> 00:20:50,033
[CHESKA] Aww!

433
00:20:50,033 --> 00:20:53,500
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

434
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:54,633
[JUSTIN CHUCKLES]

435
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:58,500
- What about you, Luna?
- Mm?

436
00:20:58,500 --> 00:21:01,467
[BREATHES DEEPLY] For me?

437
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:07,067
It's all the times
we came here together.

438
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:12,100
Because that means
Dad was with us then.

439
00:21:12,133 --> 00:21:20,033
[NOSTALGIC MUSIC PLAYING]

440
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:25,933
[LUNA] What about you, Jade?
Don't tell me you have none.

441
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:27,633
[CHUCKLES]

442
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:32,333
Don't tell me that
you don't remember.

443
00:21:33,033 --> 00:21:36,000
Wouldn't it be the time when
you'd play together with Kiko?

444
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:40,033
- [CHESKA GIGGLING]
- [MARTIN] Ohh, what was that?

445
00:21:40,033 --> 00:21:41,233
What is that about?

446
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:45,033
- Baby bro! Baby bro!
- Brother, what's up with that?

447
00:21:45,067 --> 00:21:48,533
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

448
00:21:48,533 --> 00:21:50,667
That is my happy memory here.

449
00:21:51,300 --> 00:21:55,100
The playtimes I had
with Kiko here.

450
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:05,333
We were happy and we didn't
think about problems then.

451
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:09,133
[YOUNG JADE]<i> Kiko, have you
</i> found an Easter egg yet?

452
00:22:09,133 --> 00:22:11,133
<i>- Come!
- Let's go!</i>

453
00:22:11,133 --> 00:22:16,500
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

454
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:19,367
You know, how I wish...

455
00:22:19,567 --> 00:22:21,533
we could go back to that time.

456
00:22:21,533 --> 00:22:25,500
- [CHESKA SCREECHES] Throwback!
- [GIGGLING]

457
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:27,067
[JUSTIN] There are mosquitoes
now because it's so sweet here.

458
00:22:27,067 --> 00:22:29,533
[CHUCKLING]

459
00:22:29,533 --> 00:22:31,100
What about you, Martin?

460
00:22:31,533 --> 00:22:36,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

461
00:22:36,133 --> 00:22:37,500
It would be when...

462
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:40,200
Gio and I always teased Kiko.

463
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:42,533
[YOUNG MARTIN] The last person
has poop in their butt!

464
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:43,700
[LAUGHING]

465
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:45,133
[GIO] You know, it'd be great
if we bring that back.

466
00:22:45,133 --> 00:22:47,433
- We could!
- Why not?

467
00:22:47,433 --> 00:22:49,033
I told you, bro.

468
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:51,467
You exude baby boy energy
here in the hotel.

469
00:22:51,467 --> 00:22:53,633
- Oh, is that so?
- Why? Is she wrong?

470
00:22:53,633 --> 00:22:56,400
- Can you pull that off now?
- Go on, try me!

471
00:22:56,400 --> 00:23:00,100
- Go on!
- Try me!

472
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:03,233
Well, for my happy memory...

473
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:05,633
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

474
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:07,433
It might be...

475
00:23:09,133 --> 00:23:11,133
when we'd be lying
in the front yard

476
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:13,367
with Papa when
we were still kids.

477
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:16,133
[MICHAEL] Brothers should
love each other

478
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:18,767
<i>even if you have
different mothers.</i>

479
00:23:18,767 --> 00:23:21,133
You will look after one another.

480
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:23,367
You'll take care of each other.

481
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:25,733
<i>- Promise?
- Promise, Papa.</i>

482
00:23:25,733 --> 00:23:28,300
<i>- Promise.
- Promise.</i>

483
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:29,700
[MICHAEL CHUCKLING]

484
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:32,167
[GIO]<i> To be honest,
</i> I already miss Papa.

485
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:39,100
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

486
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:43,100
What about you guys?

487
00:23:43,700 --> 00:23:45,267
- [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
- For me...

488
00:23:46,367 --> 00:23:47,767
- I have two.
- [GIO] That's too much.

489
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:49,767
- There are instructions.
- How greedy.

490
00:23:49,767 --> 00:23:51,633
- That better be good.
- That's a lot.

491
00:23:51,633 --> 00:23:54,600
My first happy memory would be

492
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:57,200
when Papa called for us.

493
00:23:57,233 --> 00:23:58,367
[KIKO] Gio!

494
00:23:59,233 --> 00:24:00,400
<i> How have you been?</i>

495
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,667
<i> Martin!</i>

496
00:24:01,867 --> 00:24:04,700
<i>I never thought we'd
ever be together again.</i>

497
00:24:05,467 --> 00:24:08,433
As for my second happy memory...

498
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:12,300
was when I met my best friend.

499
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:14,400
[SQUEALING]

500
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:17,233
[RAPHIE] How I wish
everyone has a best friend.

501
00:24:17,233 --> 00:24:18,233
[GIGGLING]

502
00:24:18,233 --> 00:24:25,200
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

503
00:24:29,333 --> 00:24:32,300
[SARI] Sir! Sir!
Ask me too, sir.

504
00:24:32,567 --> 00:24:35,167
Sari, nobody's asking you.

505
00:24:35,167 --> 00:24:36,800
[CHUCKLING]

506
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,133
Sir Martin.

507
00:24:38,567 --> 00:24:39,700
Fine.

508
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:41,300
You may give your answer, Sari.

509
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,767
That's already my answer.

510
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,467
It's Sir Martin.

511
00:24:45,467 --> 00:24:49,533
[RAPHIE] My girl is always
bringing surprises!

512
00:24:49,733 --> 00:24:51,233
No.

513
00:24:51,233 --> 00:24:53,167
What I mean is

514
00:24:53,167 --> 00:24:55,300
my happy memory was

515
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:58,467
when I was accepted to
be Sir Martin's assistant

516
00:24:58,467 --> 00:25:00,300
here at Hotel 88.

517
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:02,867
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

518
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:08,400
And I instantly found
a family in you all.

519
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:11,900
- [SQUEALING]
- [RAPHIE] You just inserted us.

520
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:13,733
[KIKO] Wait a second, Monette.

521
00:25:13,733 --> 00:25:15,400
You haven't answered yet.

522
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:16,800
- Oh yeah.
- That's right.

523
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:18,367
You started this.

524
00:25:19,733 --> 00:25:21,300
[MONETTE] For me...

525
00:25:22,567 --> 00:25:25,533
my happy memories here
at the hotel...

526
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,567
It was when Sir Mike
fostered me and Raphie

527
00:25:30,567 --> 00:25:32,400
when we were orphaned.

528
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:39,367
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

529
00:25:40,267 --> 00:25:43,700
I also feel happy whenever
I see his three baby boys happy.

530
00:25:45,667 --> 00:25:48,967
You're displaying emotions
more often now, sister.

531
00:25:48,967 --> 00:25:50,500
[MONETTE] No.

532
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:53,867
I just remembered the times
when you were so happy.

533
00:25:54,967 --> 00:25:57,967
You have become a family
even though you are far apart.

534
00:25:57,967 --> 00:25:59,533
Monette, it's "we."

535
00:26:00,567 --> 00:26:02,567
We are a family.

536
00:26:02,567 --> 00:26:03,933
It's not just us.

537
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:06,367
Okay?

538
00:26:06,567 --> 00:26:08,367
Gio was right.

539
00:26:08,767 --> 00:26:11,367
All of us here at Hotel 88

540
00:26:11,367 --> 00:26:13,467
share one heart and one family.

541
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,000
[RAPHIE] She's driving us wild,
doesn't he?

542
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,733
She's the one who keeps talking
about happy memories,

543
00:26:18,733 --> 00:26:20,600
but she's also
the first one to cry.

544
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:22,600
[MONETTE] Okay, fine! I'm sorry.

545
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:24,433
Let me make you
all smile this time.

546
00:26:24,433 --> 00:26:27,433
I've prepared
some special dessert!

547
00:26:27,433 --> 00:26:29,567
- [CHEERING] Yes!
- That's what I like!

548
00:26:29,567 --> 00:26:31,567
What dessert could it be?

549
00:26:31,567 --> 00:26:33,700
- Are you all ready?
- Yes!

550
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:42,100
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

551
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:47,467
[MARINA SCREAMING]

552
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:49,900
- [SANDRO GROWLING]
- [MARINA GROANING]

553
00:26:49,900 --> 00:26:52,567
[MARINA WHIMPERING]

554
00:26:52,567 --> 00:26:58,400
[SCREAMING]

555
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:01,000
[SANDRO GROANING]

556
00:27:01,633 --> 00:27:02,800
[GUN COCKS]

557
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:07,400
[GUNSHOTS]

558
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:14,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

559
00:27:28,967 --> 00:27:34,800
[MARINA GROANING]

560
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:36,800
You killed my son.

561
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:43,800
[GROANING]

562
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:50,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

563
00:27:57,767 --> 00:28:00,567
[BODY THUDS]

564
00:28:05,833 --> 00:28:12,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

565
00:28:18,133 --> 00:28:19,733
[LEON] Help!

566
00:28:19,733 --> 00:28:21,100
<i> Help!</i>

567
00:28:22,167 --> 00:28:24,533
[SCREAMS] Help!

568
00:28:24,533 --> 00:28:26,633
<i> Help!</i>

569
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:32,600
Nothing bad will happen to Leon.

570
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:34,233
<i>But my guts are
telling me otherwise.</i>

571
00:28:34,233 --> 00:28:36,900
<i>How many more has to die
before this ends?</i>

572
00:28:36,900 --> 00:28:39,667
<i>Bros! The police are
on social media.</i>

573
00:28:39,667 --> 00:28:42,000
<i> You should leave, both of you.</i>

574
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:43,833
<i> You don't understand</i>

575
00:28:43,833 --> 00:28:46,633
<i>what kind of danger
we are facing right now.</i>

576
00:28:48,500 --> 00:28:49,633
<i> Kiko was right.</i>

577
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:51,467
<i> Your siblings also are.</i>

578
00:28:51,900 --> 00:28:53,867
<i> This would benefit us.</i>

579
00:28:54,233 --> 00:28:55,533
[LOUD THUD]

580
00:28:55,767 --> 00:28:57,933
<i>Raphie, don't pull
a prank on me.</i>

581
00:28:57,933 --> 00:29:03,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]
